cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on improving the accuracy of appearance-based gaze estimation using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of dilated-convolutions to extract high-level features, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning techniques for gaze estimation also falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of gaze estimation in human-computer interaction, which falls under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
